+# Generic Five-Orbit Shared-Mode Seeds Spill On The First Honest Closure Pass
+
+Status: `INFERRED` current-budget closure verdict with `VERIFIED`
+representative sign-sheet coefficient audit
+
+For the generic shared-mode second-budget seed family
+`T_gen(a,b,c) = {(a,b,a+b), (a,c,a+c)}` with five distinct wavevector orbits
+`a`, `b`, `c`, `d := a+b`, `e := a+c`, the conjugate-complete starting ledger
+is
+`S_0 = {plus/minus a, plus/minus b, plus/minus c, plus/minus d, plus/minus e}`.
+
+On that full active ledger, the decisive first new interactions are the
+cross-triad ordered pairs
+`(d, c) -> a+b+c`,
+`(d, -c) -> a+b-c`,
+and
+`(e, -b) -> a-b+c`.
+For an honest generic five-orbit seed, at least one of those targets lies
+outside the seed ledger; if all of them folded back in, the seed would have
+collapsed onto a lower-dimensional coincidence locus already quotient-
+identified as the mirror/parallelogram subfamily or as a first-budget
+artifact.
+
+The representative coefficient audit at
+`a = (1,0,0)`,
+`b = (0,1,0)`,
+`c = (0,0,1)`
+found that all `32/32` seed sign assignments remain live and all `32/32`
+force at least one new target helical sector on those first cross-pair
+targets. One sample coefficient pair on `(d, c) -> a+b+c` is
+`|C_+| = 0.557678`,
+`|C_-| = 0.149429`.
+
+So the generic five-orbit shared-mode family already spills on the first
+honest recursive-closure pass and does not stay inside the frozen second
+budget.
+
+Filed from:
+- `missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/library-inbox/step-003-exploration-002-recursive-closure-and-spillover-audit.md`
